1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 14=

3
00:02:01,740 --> 00:02:02,300
You're back.

4
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,377
Still not asleep this late?

5
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:05,260
I was waiting for you.

6
00:02:05,260 --> 00:02:06,460
I knew you'd come back.

7
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,822
You're still up, too?

8
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:11,260
I'm hungry.

9
00:02:16,555 --> 00:02:18,580
So, when did you
and Zhang Yousen get together?

10
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:20,180
Before dinner today.

11
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:21,900
Why?

12
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:25,340
I just wanted to bring a boyfriend

13
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:26,355
to dinner with you all.

14
00:02:28,088 --> 00:02:29,380
What kind of reason is that?

15
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:32,580
So now dinner's over,

16
00:02:32,755 --> 00:02:34,155
and you've already broken up?

17
00:02:34,244 --> 00:02:35,155
We didn't break up.

18
00:02:35,380 --> 00:02:36,020
So now

19
00:02:36,380 --> 00:02:37,380
you're officially dating?

20
00:02:38,533 --> 00:02:40,044
What do you like about him?

21
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:43,420
I like

22
00:02:44,420 --> 00:02:45,100
that he likes me.

23
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,111
He's picking me up for work tomorrow.

24
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:50,340
Just don't hurt him.

25
00:02:51,955 --> 00:02:53,540
You're my friend, or he's your friend?

26
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,220
Exactly because you're my friend,

27
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,380
I'm worried about him.

28
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:02,580
Zhou Mei,

29
00:03:02,777 --> 00:03:03,500
congratulations.

30
00:03:03,555 --> 00:03:05,733
You're the first among us
to get into a relationship.

31
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,066
What about you?

32
00:03:07,822 --> 00:03:08,940
Those male classmates of yours,

33
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:10,133
not a single one you like?

34
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:11,780
I don't like my male classmates.

35
00:03:12,177 --> 00:03:13,355
They're too immature.

36
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:16,180
I like someone like Mr. He Han.

37
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:18,500
I mean his type.

38
00:03:19,422 --> 00:03:20,711
What do you like about him?

39
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:21,740
His talent.

40
00:03:22,977 --> 00:03:25,555
I've never thought there
was anything special about him.

41
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:28,620
If his writing is good, just read it.

42
00:03:28,740 --> 00:03:30,066
Why bother looking at the person?

43
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:30,820
If one day

44
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:32,500
you found his talent was gone,

45
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:33,980
would you still like him?

46
00:03:35,020 --> 00:03:36,780
Talent is innate.

47
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:38,200
How could it just disappear?

48
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,620
Talent and looks

49
00:03:39,980 --> 00:03:41,700
can both change over time.

50
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:53,860
Alright.

51
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:55,020
I'm sleepy.

52
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:56,800
I'll go to sleep.

53
00:03:58,460 --> 00:03:59,340
Good night.

54
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:57,900
Hello?

55
00:04:58,260 --> 00:04:59,380
What are you doing?

56
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:02,300
Do you realize how childish this is?

57
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:10,940
I didn't know what else to do.

58
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:15,300
Just when I went out,

59
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,820
Zhang Yousen texted me,

60
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:18,740
asking me to dinner.

61
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:20,260
So I let him come.

62
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:21,660
I said

63
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:23,740
I wanted him to come

64
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:24,980
as my boyfriend.

65
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:31,820
I couldn't face that dinner alone.

66
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:34,660
I would've lost it.

67
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:38,540
But if you keep getting
entangled with Lawyer Bei like this,

68
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:40,940
sooner or later
Zhang Yousen will find out

69
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:41,860
you're using him.

70
00:05:42,266 --> 00:05:44,488
And when that happens,
he'll be the one losing it.

71
00:05:44,955 --> 00:05:47,266
I won't have anything
to do with Lawyer Bei anymore.

72
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:49,980
And I won't

73
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:52,500
hurt Zhang Yousen either.

74
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,460
He's a good person.

75
00:05:56,260 --> 00:05:57,180
Better than Lawyer Bei.

76
00:05:59,580 --> 00:06:00,020
So...

77
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:02,620
I'll keep seeing him,

78
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:05,580
even if it's just for a while.

79
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:07,500
I'll still do my best.

80
00:06:09,460 --> 00:06:10,460
Then remember this.

81
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:12,940
You've already added Mrs. Bei on WeChat.

82
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:14,460
So, what you post

83
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:15,580
and what you don't,

84
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,220
you have to be very careful.

85
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,700
I think Mrs. Bei already knows.

86
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,820
Otherwise, she wouldn't have added us.

87
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:28,020
Don't underestimate a woman's intuition.

88
00:06:30,940 --> 00:06:31,460
But now

89
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:35,140
I have a boyfriend.

90
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:38,260
The pressure now is on Lawyer Bei.

91
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:27,060
Zhanqiao,

92
00:07:28,422 --> 00:07:30,177
let's grab some breakfast together.

93
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:31,860
Sure.

94
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:32,666
Let's go.

95
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:34,140
You already ate?

96
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:35,340
Yeah.

97
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:42,380
I messaged you,
and you replied so slowly.

98
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,060
You must've been busy.

99
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:50,100
Yeah, busy saving my company.

100
00:07:50,620 --> 00:07:51,500
You know how it is.

101
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:52,660
You're joking.

102
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:54,700
So many people

103
00:07:55,444 --> 00:07:56,711
are trying to save you.

104
00:07:57,660 --> 00:07:58,540
You're just choosing

105
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:00,700
who gets that chance,

106
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:01,500
right?

107
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,540
I'm in line, too.

108
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:08,100
Let me be honest, Mr. Fan.

109
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:11,460
I do want to partner with you,

110
00:08:12,380 --> 00:08:13,133
but the price

111
00:08:14,020 --> 00:08:14,940
you offered

112
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:16,100
is far too low.

113
00:08:16,740 --> 00:08:18,260
Other investors, although...

114
00:08:18,260 --> 00:08:19,555
Things are different now.

115
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:20,660
I can offer more.

116
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:22,100
No upper limit.

117
00:08:23,644 --> 00:08:25,100
I'll bring you the contract later.

118
00:08:28,044 --> 00:08:30,377
That doesn't sound
like something you'd say.

119
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:33,620
You're being unfair.

120
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:35,340
Why didn't you tell me

121
00:08:35,844 --> 00:08:37,244
that He Han is coming back?

122
00:08:42,444 --> 00:08:43,340
You kept it from me.

123
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:47,220
Otherwise, how could

124
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:49,266
so many people come
looking to invest in you?

125
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:50,700
If you'd told me earlier,

126
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:51,980
what chance would they have had?

127
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:58,180
I don't know where you heard that,

128
00:08:58,780 --> 00:09:00,420
but rumors are just rumors.

129
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:01,340
What rumors?

130
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:02,700
He Han said it himself.

131
00:09:02,955 --> 00:09:04,460
And you're still keeping it secret?

132
00:09:23,060 --> 00:09:24,220
Mr. Fan just told me

133
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:25,860
you admitted to him

134
00:09:25,977 --> 00:09:27,577
that you agreed to return to Chenxing.

135
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:28,460
Is that true?

136
00:09:29,155 --> 00:09:30,260
Why don't I know about it?

137
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:32,420
Your best friend
asked me to do you a favor,

138
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,460
saying it would be easy

139
00:09:33,460 --> 00:09:35,100
and could get you out of trouble.

140
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,940
It's hard to explain over the phone.

141
00:09:54,940 --> 00:09:56,340
Tell me what's going on.

142
00:09:57,820 --> 00:09:58,660
Something this big,

143
00:09:58,660 --> 00:09:59,980
and you didn't tell me in advance.

144
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:01,540
When Mr. Fan asked me just now,

145
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:02,940
I didn't dare say a word.

146
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,660
I was afraid that if I
said the wrong thing,

147
00:10:04,660 --> 00:10:05,620
the money would be gone.

148
00:10:06,020 --> 00:10:07,580
Before, so many investment firms

149
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:08,977
were interested in working with you.

150
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:10,220
Some of them are my friends,

151
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,380
and the rest I drew in
by spreading the word

152
00:10:12,866 --> 00:10:14,511
that He Han was returning to Chenxing.

153
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:17,100
Now is the best time
to invest at a low price.

154
00:10:17,820 --> 00:10:19,500
But you know that's impossible.

155
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,066
Doesn't matter whether it's possible.

156
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:23,260
Those companies are
just here to prop you up.

157
00:10:23,866 --> 00:10:25,420
As long as the show looks convincing

158
00:10:25,488 --> 00:10:27,511
and draws Mr. Fan's attention,
that's enough.

159
00:10:27,666 --> 00:10:29,222
When Mr. Fan came to see you today,

160
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:31,420
he must have heard about it from them.

161
00:10:32,888 --> 00:10:34,088
What about He Han?

162
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:36,180
If Mr. Fan asked him,

163
00:10:36,580 --> 00:10:37,460
why did he admit it?

164
00:10:38,780 --> 00:10:40,540
Of course, I had to give him a heads-up.

165
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:43,020
Here.

166
00:10:43,711 --> 00:10:44,622
- Thanks.
- Nuts.

167
00:10:46,460 --> 00:10:46,860
He Han,

168
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:49,220
is this your new girlfriend?

169
00:10:49,820 --> 00:10:50,300
No.

170
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,250
I don't think you
could win her over anyway.

171
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:54,666
We're not interested in each other.

172
00:10:54,740 --> 00:10:55,580
Genetic mismatch.

173
00:10:55,700 --> 00:10:56,940
Boss, check please.

174
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:58,500
Coming. You guys carry on.

175
00:10:58,700 --> 00:10:59,540
Coming.

176
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:03,140
Anyone with eyes can see

177
00:11:03,222 --> 00:11:05,733
that you and Lin Zhanqiao
still care about each other.

178
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:07,020
So you'll definitely

179
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,180
help with this, right?

180
00:11:09,888 --> 00:11:11,580
Lin Zhanqiao asked you to come find me?

181
00:11:12,977 --> 00:11:13,860
I haven't told her yet.

182
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:16,955
We'll act it out first,
and then tell her.

183
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:18,860
Otherwise,

184
00:11:18,977 --> 00:11:20,644
she'll make a big deal out of it again.

185
00:11:22,540 --> 00:11:23,980
You came up with this plan

186
00:11:24,700 --> 00:11:26,380
because she mentioned wanting me back?

187
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:29,380
Well, no.

188
00:11:31,420 --> 00:11:32,020
Good.

189
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:35,060
Anyway, the script is already set.

190
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:38,100
Now it's up to you and He Han

191
00:11:38,420 --> 00:11:40,500
to figure out how to
play this reconciliation.

192
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:43,660
Mr. Fan sees Chenxing's future value.

193
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:46,260
If he invests heavily
and signs with you,

194
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:47,580
then you've succeeded.

195
00:11:48,140 --> 00:11:49,580
He's too shrewd.

196
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:51,220
How could he fall for this

197
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:52,220
so easily?

198
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:53,711
He's taking a gamble, too.

199
00:11:54,355 --> 00:11:55,933
If He Han really returns to Chenxing,

200
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:56,860
on paper,

201
00:11:56,955 --> 00:11:58,777
then he'll have to invest even more.

202
00:11:58,866 --> 00:12:00,000
So, you need to make him

203
00:12:00,266 --> 00:12:02,888
feel his chances of winning
are higher, and then he will be

204
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:04,022
willing to put in money.

205
00:12:04,060 --> 00:12:05,300
What if he just drags it out?

206
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:07,740
My company can't afford to wait.

207
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:10,460
Then, it becomes a game between you two.

208
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:12,300
Given his personality,

209
00:12:14,260 --> 00:12:15,380
you should

210
00:12:15,511 --> 00:12:17,488
deny that you
and He Han have reconciled.

211
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:18,820
The more you deny it,

212
00:12:18,866 --> 00:12:20,288
the more interested he'll be.

213
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:22,980
How...

214
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:25,540
How am I supposed to say that

215
00:12:25,540 --> 00:12:26,140
to He Han?

216
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:27,020
Come on.

217
00:12:27,660 --> 00:12:29,140
Your company is on the brink.

218
00:12:29,311 --> 00:12:31,220
What's wrong with
swallowing a bit of pride?

219
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:34,420
Ms. Mei,

220
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:36,420
a package from Lawyer Bei's firm.

221
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:40,020
Candice.

222
00:12:43,311 --> 00:12:44,140
Return it to him.

223
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:45,060
Alright.

224
00:12:46,380 --> 00:12:47,266
What did he send you?

225
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,333
Probably tickets for
this weekend's performance.

226
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:53,911
What does that mean?

227
00:12:54,580 --> 00:12:55,460
Trying to make amends?

228
00:12:56,380 --> 00:12:57,380
Ruined one evening,

229
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:59,100
so he offers another to make up for it?

230
00:13:00,620 --> 00:13:01,420
That's probably

231
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:02,780
how he sees things.

232
00:13:03,555 --> 00:13:05,020
I can also refuse the settlement.

233
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:08,340
(Return Slip)

234
00:13:13,780 --> 00:13:19,580
(International Top-Tier
Music Performance)

235
00:13:30,244 --> 00:13:32,777
A friend gave me two tickets
for a concert this weekend.

236
00:13:33,220 --> 00:13:34,355
I don't have time to go.

237
00:13:34,740 --> 00:13:35,300
Take them.

238
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:37,220
You can go with your girlfriend.

239
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:38,700
Lawyer Bei,

240
00:13:39,288 --> 00:13:41,460
this is a show Zhou Mei
has always wanted to see.

241
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:42,577
I couldn't even get tickets.

242
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:43,260
Thank you.

243
00:13:45,340 --> 00:13:46,500
Zhou Mei will be very happy.

244
00:13:50,311 --> 00:13:52,060
The channel has been approved.
No problem.

245
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:53,780
Hello, Mr. He Han.

246
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:54,900
Alright.

247
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:55,860
Don't worry.

248
00:13:55,860 --> 00:13:57,780
(Fresh Meat Mooncakes)

249
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:58,650
Hello.

250
00:13:58,650 --> 00:13:59,140
Mr. He Han.

251
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:02,020
Mr. He Han.

252
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,300
Mr. He Han.

253
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:05,090
Your boss is inside?

254
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:05,660
Upstairs.

255
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:08,260
These are the newly screened authors.

256
00:14:08,311 --> 00:14:09,650
There are many strong candidates.

257
00:14:09,977 --> 00:14:10,900
How's the progress?

258
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:12,420
Fresh meat mooncakes?

259
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:14,700
You can wait for
hours and still not get them.

260
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:15,700
Our boss likes them.

261
00:14:16,066 --> 00:14:17,980
If this isn't trying to please her,
what is?

262
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:18,980
What's this?

263
00:14:19,540 --> 00:14:22,266
Looks like it's not just
work easing the tension.

264
00:14:22,488 --> 00:14:23,500
They can't stay apart.

265
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:24,580
The more they fight,
the harder it is to split.

266
00:14:24,580 --> 00:14:25,220
Impossible.

267
00:14:26,980 --> 00:14:27,940
Hello.

268
00:14:28,780 --> 00:14:29,860
- Mr. He Han.
- Mr. He Han.

269
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:30,620
Mr. He.

270
00:14:30,933 --> 00:14:31,940
We'll get back to work.

271
00:14:45,340 --> 00:14:46,740
I got you the fresh meat mooncakes.

272
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:48,700
Now the baton is in your hands.

273
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:50,100
How do you plan to respond?

274
00:14:53,420 --> 00:14:54,420
If we're acting,

275
00:14:55,780 --> 00:14:57,660
there needs to be a gradual build-up.

276
00:14:58,133 --> 00:14:59,533
You can't jump straight into

277
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:02,060
a dramatic reconciliation like this.

278
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,140
Who would believe it?

279
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:14,260
How much is Mr. Fan offering now?

280
00:15:27,420 --> 00:15:28,300
Eat it,

281
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:29,911
and he can go up to seven.

282
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,340
I've already eaten.

283
00:15:32,377 --> 00:15:33,466
I can't eat anymore.

284
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:37,020
For Chenxing, you know?

285
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:57,177
It's good, right?

286
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:00,111
So this counts as helping me?

287
00:16:01,540 --> 00:16:02,460
Doesn't it?

288
00:16:03,740 --> 00:16:04,860
How should I thank you?

289
00:16:06,155 --> 00:16:07,466
Wait until it's done.

290
00:16:07,644 --> 00:16:09,466
Don't worry.
I won't take advantage of you.

291
00:16:31,780 --> 00:16:32,420
Thank you.

292
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:45,420
Keep it up.

293
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:57,580
Just follow what I told you.

294
00:16:57,740 --> 00:16:59,420
Right. If there are any issues...

295
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:01,660
I'm leaving.

296
00:17:01,733 --> 00:17:03,466
There are mooncakes upstairs.
Help yourselves.

297
00:17:03,488 --> 00:17:04,140
- Bye.
- Alright.

298
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:04,540
Thanks.

299
00:17:04,540 --> 00:17:05,280
- Bye.
- Thanks.

300
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:08,170
I told you so.

301
00:17:08,170 --> 00:17:08,620
See?

302
00:17:08,620 --> 00:17:09,460
Fresh meat mooncakes.

303
00:17:09,580 --> 00:17:11,140
I only have one question now.

304
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:46,660
(Editor Fan Shu, Content Department)

305
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:49,460
I heard He Han

306
00:17:49,820 --> 00:17:52,540
bought Lin Zhanqiao
fresh meat mooncakes.

307
00:17:53,820 --> 00:17:55,380
Those are hard to get.

308
00:17:55,380 --> 00:17:57,620
You have to queue for them.

309
00:17:58,333 --> 00:17:59,660
Have they gotten back together?

310
00:18:00,380 --> 00:18:02,500
Did you notice anything?

311
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:04,260
I'm not sure.

312
00:18:05,740 --> 00:18:07,900
Don't you think this
is a bit too sudden?

313
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:12,300
Could they be

314
00:18:13,260 --> 00:18:14,660
putting on a show for everyone?

315
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:16,540
So people would think

316
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:18,900
He Han wants to return to Chenxing

317
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:21,500
and rush to place their bets?

318
00:18:21,820 --> 00:18:23,380
Is that possible?

319
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:24,700
If they've teamed up,

320
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:25,740
then you picked right.

321
00:18:26,020 --> 00:18:28,620
I just signed He Han. If they team up,

322
00:18:28,940 --> 00:18:29,980
I'll be out of the game.

323
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:31,610
So on this matter,

324
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:32,380
we're not aligned.

325
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:34,060
If you can

326
00:18:34,820 --> 00:18:36,740
bring Lin Zhanqiao
and He Han over to me,

327
00:18:38,180 --> 00:18:38,900
how about

328
00:18:39,155 --> 00:18:40,711
shares in Dingqi Platform?

329
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:42,460
You lost He Han,

330
00:18:42,980 --> 00:18:45,020
but you gain Dingqi Platform.

331
00:18:45,020 --> 00:18:45,500
How much?

332
00:18:46,933 --> 00:18:48,340
Ten ten-thousandths, how about it?

333
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:49,488
Twenty ten-thousandths.

334
00:18:50,740 --> 00:18:51,100
Alright.

335
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:52,580
No less than

336
00:18:53,022 --> 00:18:54,140
fifteen ten-thousandths.

337
00:18:54,940 --> 00:18:55,380
Deal.

338
00:19:02,940 --> 00:19:03,580
You're back.

339
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:05,260
Come sit.

340
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:07,044
There's something I need to tell you.

341
00:19:13,060 --> 00:19:13,340
Sit.

342
00:19:17,340 --> 00:19:19,220
How come I didn't know

343
00:19:19,220 --> 00:19:21,420
you were going back to Chenxing

344
00:19:21,911 --> 00:19:23,610
and getting back
together with Lin Zhanqiao?

345
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,220
How could you not know?

346
00:19:25,580 --> 00:19:27,180
If Mr. Fan knows, then you should know.

347
00:19:27,540 --> 00:19:28,140
Is it true?

348
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:30,580
No.

349
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:33,170
I have a cooperation agreement with you.

350
00:19:33,170 --> 00:19:34,460
I'm not about to break it

351
00:19:34,460 --> 00:19:35,700
and go back to Lin Zhanqiao.

352
00:19:39,140 --> 00:19:40,220
You don't trust me?

353
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,540
I trust what you're saying now,

354
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:44,660
but I don't trust Lin Zhanqiao.

355
00:19:44,660 --> 00:19:46,740
Fake acting turning real
isn't impossible,

356
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:47,220
right?

357
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:47,820
Here.

358
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:52,580
You've prepared everything?

359
00:19:53,260 --> 00:19:54,780
Take a look at the draft first.

360
00:19:55,980 --> 00:19:57,060
From now on,

361
00:19:57,060 --> 00:20:00,260
your share with me goes from 2:8 to 3:7.

362
00:20:01,220 --> 00:20:02,300
That way,

363
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:04,260
if you cut me out

364
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:05,860
and go back to Lin Zhanqiao,

365
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:09,355
I'll at least have collected
some compensation in advance.

366
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:22,620
Your information came from Mr. Fan.

367
00:20:23,244 --> 00:20:24,980
So where did his information come from?

368
00:20:27,140 --> 00:20:28,622
Probing something for Lin Zhanqiao?

369
00:20:30,380 --> 00:20:31,060
I don't know.

370
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:33,980
I really don't know.

371
00:20:36,380 --> 00:20:37,740
Then it must be

372
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:40,140
someone who has access to her office.

373
00:20:48,260 --> 00:20:48,660
Ms. Lin.

374
00:20:52,540 --> 00:20:53,755
Mantou, Fragile, and Naobaijin

375
00:20:53,844 --> 00:20:55,600
(Potential Author List)
have all asked me

376
00:20:55,688 --> 00:20:57,990
for the list of potential new authors
we intend to work with.

377
00:20:58,020 --> 00:20:58,955
No one else has asked.

378
00:20:59,060 --> 00:20:59,540
Mantou.

379
00:21:04,060 --> 00:21:04,380
Here.

380
00:21:05,420 --> 00:21:06,020
Thanks.

381
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:07,900
Naobaijin,

382
00:21:08,220 --> 00:21:08,780
your list.

383
00:21:11,860 --> 00:21:13,540
I'm now cycling through

384
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:14,930
contacting the authors on these lists

385
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:16,380
to see which ones

386
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:17,580
Zhao Lanxin has reached out to.

387
00:21:18,460 --> 00:21:20,420
But if one of them

388
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:21,940
really is the insider,

389
00:21:22,780 --> 00:21:24,460
I'll feel pretty upset.

390
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:29,100
What's this?

391
00:21:29,380 --> 00:21:31,020
We've finally selected

392
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:32,260
ten promising authors.

393
00:21:32,660 --> 00:21:33,140
We?

394
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:36,740
Yes, I

395
00:21:36,940 --> 00:21:37,540
selected them

396
00:21:38,355 --> 00:21:39,377
for the company.

397
00:21:41,244 --> 00:21:42,888
During the previous screening round,

398
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:44,340
the authors you selected,

399
00:21:44,955 --> 00:21:46,288
along with the sample chapters,

400
00:21:46,290 --> 00:21:47,740
and all your evaluations and comments,

401
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:48,755
I've reviewed them all.

402
00:21:48,820 --> 00:21:49,900
As a newcomer,

403
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:51,500
to achieve this level of quality

404
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:53,180
and efficiency

405
00:21:53,190 --> 00:21:54,020
in such a short time,

406
00:21:54,020 --> 00:21:55,380
handling such a large workload,

407
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:57,540
if there wasn't someone helping you,

408
00:21:57,940 --> 00:21:59,377
you wouldn't be this organized.

409
00:22:06,420 --> 00:22:07,140
So, who was it?

410
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:12,980
He Han?

411
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:19,620
Ms. Lin, I didn't go
to Mr. He Han on my own.

412
00:22:19,620 --> 00:22:21,020
It was him.

413
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:22,700
He wanted to help us.

414
00:22:23,260 --> 00:22:24,660
And he told me not to mention it.

415
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:29,370
If he told you not to say anything,
you just kept quiet?

416
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:31,060
How would he even
know your work details?

417
00:22:32,020 --> 00:22:33,488
You must have told him, right?

418
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:36,780
Mr. He Han...

419
00:22:37,620 --> 00:22:37,980
Well,

420
00:22:38,220 --> 00:22:38,900
sometimes

421
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:40,860
I do keep in touch with him.

422
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:41,940
But I think

423
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:43,300
he just wanted

424
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,540
to understand Chenxing better.

425
00:22:46,111 --> 00:22:47,620
But anything confidential, I didn't say.

426
00:22:47,620 --> 00:22:49,444
He didn't even ask.
He understands his place.

427
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:51,020
Do you realize

428
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:52,780
you've seriously violated

429
00:22:52,780 --> 00:22:55,311
the confidentiality agreement
you signed with the company?

430
00:22:56,820 --> 00:22:57,780
I'm sorry, Ms. Lin, I...

431
00:22:57,860 --> 00:22:58,660
Yes, I know

432
00:22:58,660 --> 00:23:00,100
I should have told you first.

433
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,220
But Mr. He Han knew

434
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:03,860
that Zhiyuan withdrew funding because

435
00:23:03,860 --> 00:23:05,660
Zhao Lanxin poached
our new author group.

436
00:23:06,020 --> 00:23:07,340
He felt it was unfair for us,

437
00:23:07,340 --> 00:23:09,140
so he helped select new authors.

438
00:23:09,380 --> 00:23:10,780
He's a very principled person.

439
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,911
That's the first time I've heard someone

440
00:23:15,140 --> 00:23:16,740
describe him that way.

441
00:23:18,060 --> 00:23:19,140
From now on,

442
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:20,580
if you run into any problems at work,

443
00:23:20,780 --> 00:23:21,420
come to me,

444
00:23:21,580 --> 00:23:22,380
not him.

445
00:23:22,900 --> 00:23:23,500
Understood?

446
00:23:29,740 --> 00:23:30,140
Here.

447
00:23:31,711 --> 00:23:33,022
Mooncakes from your idol.

448
00:23:48,780 --> 00:23:49,820
Mr. He, your suit.

449
00:23:49,940 --> 00:23:50,300
Thanks.

450
00:23:51,780 --> 00:23:52,980
A suit? Whose?

451
00:23:52,980 --> 00:23:53,500
Mine.

452
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:54,540
Yours?

453
00:23:55,020 --> 00:23:56,180
Where did you get a suit?

454
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:57,977
Don't you avoid wearing
suits unless necessary?

455
00:23:58,060 --> 00:23:59,420
- What for?
- Author Night.

456
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:01,980
I thought you weren't going?

457
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:03,380
I think I should still go.

458
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:04,180
Out of respect.

459
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:06,100
This suit actually matches your outfit.

460
00:24:06,780 --> 00:24:07,460
I'm not going.

461
00:24:08,740 --> 00:24:09,500
Please go.

462
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:10,340
Why not?

463
00:24:10,340 --> 00:24:12,140
If you go,
you'll be the center of attention.

464
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:13,140
Mr. Fan's ex-wife

465
00:24:13,140 --> 00:24:14,600
and He Han's current girlfriend.

466
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:16,100
I'll leave the spotlight to you.

467
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:17,980
Mr. Fan is already prepared

468
00:24:17,980 --> 00:24:20,088
to show everyone what kind of sparks

469
00:24:20,090 --> 00:24:23,780
will come from the triangle between you,
He Han, and Gu Yan.

470
00:24:25,422 --> 00:24:27,020
Why do you think
Mr. Fan is so deliberate

471
00:24:27,020 --> 00:24:28,422
about linking Lin Zhanqiao with me?

472
00:24:28,511 --> 00:24:29,780
On one hand, it's business.

473
00:24:29,933 --> 00:24:30,900
But on the other hand,

474
00:24:31,140 --> 00:24:33,260
he wants me to give
you back the "single" label

475
00:24:33,660 --> 00:24:35,060
so he can have a proper reason

476
00:24:35,060 --> 00:24:36,260
to get back together with you.

477
00:24:38,860 --> 00:24:39,733
Give me a break.

478
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:41,660
An ex-wife for a day

479
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:42,900
is an ex-wife for life.

480
00:25:21,140 --> 00:25:22,500
That outfit looks pretty sharp.

481
00:25:23,140 --> 00:25:23,500
Yeah.

482
00:25:25,244 --> 00:25:26,377
Heading out, Sir.

483
00:25:29,688 --> 00:25:30,533
You're here.

484
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,844
Showing up in style, huh?

485
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:34,140
You look great today, too.

486
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,711
I'm just riding on your coattails.

487
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,000
Let's take a photo together.

488
00:25:37,010 --> 00:25:38,020
We'll take one at the venue.

489
00:25:38,020 --> 00:25:39,577
There'll be professional photographers.

490
00:25:39,580 --> 00:25:41,100
I'm worried that since it'll be crowded,

491
00:25:41,100 --> 00:25:42,288
the photos won't turn out well,

492
00:25:42,290 --> 00:25:43,980
or the background
will be full of people,

493
00:25:43,980 --> 00:25:45,130
and we won't get
a proper photo of just us.

494
00:25:45,140 --> 00:25:46,355
Then, let's take one now.

495
00:25:48,620 --> 00:25:48,980
Wait.

496
00:25:57,140 --> 00:25:58,620
Relax, don't be so stiff.

497
00:25:58,755 --> 00:25:59,422
Be natural.

498
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:01,940
I'm not stiff.

499
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:03,060
I'm just a bit excited

500
00:26:03,140 --> 00:26:04,755
that we can take a photo like this.

501
00:26:04,844 --> 00:26:06,155
What are you doing?

502
00:26:08,340 --> 00:26:09,180
Alright, let's go.

503
00:26:09,340 --> 00:26:10,020
We'll be late.

504
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:12,020
Stop staring.

505
00:26:12,260 --> 00:26:13,780
They're off to some high-end event.

506
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:15,660
That outfit from before

507
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:16,980
was clearly for tonight.

508
00:26:18,780 --> 00:26:19,740
What kind of event?

509
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:25,580
Come.

510
00:26:25,940 --> 00:26:26,300
Here.

511
00:26:26,780 --> 00:26:27,300
Take a look.

512
00:26:32,711 --> 00:26:34,244
What's so special about it?

513
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:42,740
Stop banging like that.

514
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:44,600
You've already broken several keyboards.

515
00:26:44,620 --> 00:26:46,444
It's not yours,
so you don't care, right?

516
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:47,220
And last time,

517
00:26:47,220 --> 00:26:48,660
have you paid me back yet?

518
00:26:48,711 --> 00:26:50,933
If you keep this up,
you're not welcome here.

519
00:26:56,220 --> 00:26:57,577
(Dingqi 2024 Annual Author Night)

520
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:26,820
Hello.

521
00:27:27,133 --> 00:27:29,422
The number you dialed
is currently unavailable.

522
00:27:46,111 --> 00:27:47,311
There is someone here.

523
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:53,400
I have a company event tonight.

524
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:55,088
You head back first. We'll talk later.

525
00:28:08,620 --> 00:28:09,400
You'll drive?

526
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:10,700
I will.

527
00:28:13,333 --> 00:28:14,488
Wipe your mouth clean.

528
00:28:16,860 --> 00:28:18,300
Do you know who that girl is?

529
00:28:20,580 --> 00:28:22,200
She came to the company before,

530
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,700
and applied for a front desk position.

531
00:28:23,700 --> 00:28:24,660
HR turned her down.

532
00:28:24,780 --> 00:28:25,540
The reason was

533
00:28:27,511 --> 00:28:29,066
that she was too good-looking.

534
00:28:29,700 --> 00:28:30,740
She is pretty.

535
00:28:30,888 --> 00:28:32,755
Just right for you to use to provoke me.

536
00:28:32,780 --> 00:28:33,620
A graceful lady

537
00:28:33,888 --> 00:28:35,088
is a gentleman's pursuit.

538
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:37,140
If you like pretty girls,

539
00:28:37,340 --> 00:28:38,466
then go after them.

540
00:28:38,700 --> 00:28:39,460
But don't think

541
00:28:39,460 --> 00:28:40,980
dating a few girls can provoke me.

542
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:42,820
I don't care at all.

543
00:28:43,140 --> 00:28:44,740
The one who laughs last laughs best.

544
00:28:46,420 --> 00:28:46,940
Zhao Lanxin,

545
00:28:47,620 --> 00:28:48,580
let me tell you this.

546
00:28:49,820 --> 00:28:50,380
If you weren't

547
00:28:50,860 --> 00:28:52,380
so aggressive all the time,

548
00:28:52,380 --> 00:28:54,844
pushing things your own way,
I might actually consider

549
00:28:54,980 --> 00:28:56,060
being with you.

550
00:28:56,222 --> 00:28:57,340
But the way you are now,

551
00:28:57,340 --> 00:28:59,140
I really can't accept it.

552
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:03,540
Everything I've done is for you,

553
00:29:03,740 --> 00:29:05,180
for us, and for our future.

554
00:29:05,420 --> 00:29:07,460
All my focus is on you and the company.

555
00:29:16,620 --> 00:29:17,288
Stop the car.

556
00:29:17,300 --> 00:29:17,740
No.

557
00:29:18,540 --> 00:29:19,420
I said stop the car.

558
00:29:19,555 --> 00:29:20,900
If you leave me,
you'll never find someone like me again,

559
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:22,533
who loves and cares about you this much,

560
00:29:22,622 --> 00:29:24,180
and can go through everything with you.

561
00:29:25,488 --> 00:29:26,466
What are you doing?

562
00:29:26,820 --> 00:29:27,860
To prove how serious I am.

563
00:29:28,820 --> 00:29:29,340
Stop the car.

564
00:29:29,860 --> 00:29:30,420
Stop the car!

565
00:29:30,688 --> 00:29:32,266
What are you doing, Zhao Lanxin?

566
00:29:32,620 --> 00:29:33,780
Alright, I was wrong.

567
00:29:33,980 --> 00:29:34,500
Stop!

568
00:29:34,740 --> 00:29:35,420
Stop, stop!

569
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:36,500
Stop the car!

570
